Conservation:—
At a global level, this species meets the criteria for Least Concern (
IUCN 2001
). However, in 
Spain
, it exists in a number of small, highly disjunct populations and molecular data suggest that plants from Alicante may be distinct from the rest (fig. 1). In the Balearics, 

C. valentinus

is recognised as critically endangered (Category C2a(ii); 
Sáez and Roselló 2001
)
